// Man page for ids
manIds="IDS(8)                           X Shell Manual                           IDS(8)

<b>NAME</b>
    ids - Intrusion detection and auto-response
<b>SYNOPSIS</b>
    <b>ids</b> [PAUSE]
<b>DESCRIPTION</b>
    Locks the current machine state and watches for unauthorized changes.
    On start, baselines processes, firewall rules, and the full filesystem.
    Press <b>q</b> to stop.

    Auto-response:
    - Kill processes not present at start
    - Delete newly created files/folders
    - Restore modified text files to baseline content
    - Alert when firewall rules diverge from baseline
    - Alert when baseline files are removed

    PAUSE is the poll interval in seconds (default 1, minimum 1).
    Binary size-only changes are reported and accepted (cannot restore bytes).
<b>OPTIONS</b>
    <b>PAUSE</b>
    Seconds between scans (default 1)
<b>EXAMPLE:</b>
    <color=#e4ff34># Start Monitoring</color>
    <b>ids</b>
    Lock and watch with 1s refresh

    <b>ids 5</b>
    Same, poll every 5 seconds
<b>SEE ALSO</b>
    <b>ps</b>, <b>psLock</b>, <b>fw</b>, <b>find</b>"
